<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 20 日星期六 01:11:53 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[FBI Broke Own Rules to Probe BLM Protests, Jan. 6 Riot & Congressional Campaign]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110473155" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/14/1095668386_0:0:2560:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_a07707230352c3667382384a0bbd7898.jpg?source-sid=cc_by_20" data-photoview-image-id="1095668382" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/fbi-broke-own-rules-to-probe-blm-protests-jan-6-riot--congressional-campaign-1110473155.html?share-img=1095668382"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" title="抄送 2.0">CC BY 2.0</a> / <a href="https://flic.kr/p/2ki7dvK" title="乔·安德鲁西克">JOE ANDRUCYK</a> /</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">FBI 外勤办公室</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_by_20" alt="FBI Field Office - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="联邦调查局外勤办公室" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/14/1095668386_0:192:2560:1632_1920x0_80_0_0_19ed9301d7e424b7525252916931bc06.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/14/1095668386_0:192:2560:1632_640x0_80_0_0_5b8695294c67a58dad7f4fa3ca3feec1.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/14/1095668386_0:192:2560:1632_1280x0_80_0_0_9395a11349f2c9797ab88e3164b84acc.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/14/1095668386_0:192:2560:1632_1920x0_80_0_0_19ed9301d7e424b7525252916931bc06.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" title="抄送 2.0">CC BY 2.0</a> /<a href="https://flic.kr/p/2ki7dvK" title="乔·安德鲁西克">乔·安德鲁西克</a>/ </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊恩德马蒂诺</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_demartino_ian/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">702 条款于 2008 年修订为 1978 年外国情报监视法，允许情报机构清扫大量针对外国国民的通信。尽管如此，它也收集有关美国公民的信息。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据周五发布的经过大量编辑的法院命令，联邦调查局在调查种族正义抗议活动和 1 月 6 日的骚乱时违反了自己的规定。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> FBI 的特工违反了其有关搜索大量情报库的规定，这些情报库本应专注于外国国民，但越来越多地被用来建立针对美国公民的证据，而美国公民应该受到第四修正案的保护。该文件指出，联邦调查局违反规则搜索数据库数千次。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <strong>FBI 特工还使用该数据库收集了数千名未具名的国会竞选活动捐助者的信息。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">外国情报监视法庭 (FISA) 发布的一份秘密法庭命令详细说明了这些违规行为，FISA 是一个虚拟的橡皮图章法庭，对情报界的间谍活动提供一定程度的监督。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>为了“透明化”，国家情报总监办公室发布了这份经过大量编辑的文件。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">问题是对数据库的不当查询，该数据库是根据《外国情报监视法》第 702 条创建的，并于 2008 年修订为 1978 年法律。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据该条款，情报界可以在没有搜查令的情况下收集美国境外外国人的通讯信息。然而，在情报界称为“偶然收集”的过程中，也收集了来自美国公民的大量通信信息。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但执法机构可以查询这些数据，他们收集的任何证据都可以用来起诉和监禁人，即使他们被指控的罪行与国家安全无关。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “情报界称这种‘偶然’收集是为了淡化这样一个事实，即它经常使用这种广泛的、侵犯隐私的外国情报监视机构来收集美国人的通信，而这些通信应该需要搜查令，”电子前沿基金会在其关于第 702 条的评论中说。网站。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110473155" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/fbi-broke-own-rules-to-probe-blm-protests-jan-6-riot--congressional-campaign-1110473155.html?share-block=1110473164" data-title="“The intelligence community calls this ‘incidental’ collection to downplay the fact that it routinely uses this broad and privacy-invasive foreign intelligence surveillance authority to collect Americans’ communications that should require a warrant,” the Electronic Frontier Foundation says about Section 702 on its website."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> FBI 和其他情报机构认为，第 702 条对于他们打击恐怖主义、间谍活动和网络攻击至关重要。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> FBI 只能使用该数据库收集外国情报，只有在有特定的外国情报目的或正在寻找犯罪证据时才能搜索信息。周五发布的文件显示，联邦调查局至少 13 次使用第 702 条调查涉嫌参与 1 月 6 日骚乱的人。该命令称，尽管没有任何“分析、调查或证据目的”的支持，特工们还是进行了这些搜查。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>该机构还利用第 702 条调查了 100 多人，他们因 2020 年夏季的种族正义抗议和骚乱而被捕。在这种情况下，该文件指出，联邦调查局有理由相信查询会导致外国情报，但编辑了如何得出该评估。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该文件还指出，联邦调查局对 19,000 名未具名的国会竞选活动的捐助者进行了批量查询。执行搜索的代理人担心该活动是外国影响的目标，但表示只有“查询中使用的八个标识符与外国影响活动有足够的联系以符合查询标准”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">官员们告诉美国媒体，这位候选人没有赢得国会席位。他们还澄清说这与众议员 Darin LaHood (R-IL) 无关，后者指责 FBI 在监视数据库中不当搜索他的名字。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “今天的披露强调了国会需要遏制联邦调查局严重滥用这项法律的行为，包括使用向国会候选人捐款的人的姓名进行未经授权的搜查，”担任 ACLU 国家安全项目副主任的帕特里克图米， 说。</p><p> “这些非法搜查破坏了我们的核心宪法权利，并威胁到我们民主的基石。很明显，不能让联邦调查局自行执法。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110473155" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/fbi-broke-own-rules-to-probe-blm-protests-jan-6-riot--congressional-campaign-1110473155.html?share-block=1110473170" data-title="“Today’s disclosures underscore the need for Congress to rein in the FBI’s egregious abuses of this law, including warrantless searches using the names of people who donated to a congressional candidate,” Patrick Toomey, who serves as the deputy director of the ACLU’s National Security Project, said. “These unlawful searches undermine our core constitutional rights and threaten the bedrock of our democracy. It’s clear the FBI can’t be left to police itself.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该命令还显示，国家安全局 (NSA) 已获得 FISA 法院的批准，可以使用“新颖且敏感”的情报收集方法，但其细节已被删节。另一份未密封的命令显示，FISA 法院还授予 FBI 使用新监视方法的许可，但其细节也被删节了。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管 FBI 声称 2021 年夏季的改革将搜索规则的合规性从 82% 提高到 96%，但这一事件可能会损害情报界让国会重新授权将于今年到期的第 702 条的机会。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “第 702 条保护了美国公民的安全，让我们在海外的美国军人远离危险，”众议院情报委员会主席、众议员迈克特纳 (R-OH) 在一份声明中说。 “然而，必须做出改变，以防止 FBI 进一步滥用和滥用这一重要的国家安全工具。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110473155" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/fbi-broke-own-rules-to-probe-blm-protests-jan-6-riot--congressional-campaign-1110473155.html?share-block=1110473174" data-title="“Section 702 has kept American citizens safe and our US service members abroad out of danger,” the chair of the House Intelligence Committee Rep. Mike Turner (R-OH) said in a statement. “However, changes must be made in order to prevent further FBI misuse and abuse of this vital national security tool.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">联邦调查局并不是唯一一个因滥用外国情报调查而受到批评的机构。 2013 年，在爱德华·斯诺登 (Edward Snowden) 的爆料证明美国国家安全局 (NSA) 经常监视美国公民后不久，人们发现美国国家安全局 (NSA) 的特工使用数据库监视他们的配偶和前配偶时遇到了问题。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 00:37:58 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/fbi-broke-own-rules-to-probe-blm-protests-jan-6-riot--congressional-campaign-1110473155.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/fbi-broke-own-rules-to-probe-blm-protests-jan-6-riot--congressional-campaign-1110473155.html<category>美洲</category><category>联邦调查局</category><category>美国外国情报监视法 (FISA)</category><category>迈克·特纳</category><category>美国国家安全局</category><category>国会</category><category>大规模监视</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Reports That US Opened Door for More Arms to Kiev Instead of Peace 'Troubling' - Lawmaker]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110473568" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_49e118e38df9d3eef4f6ec6fb067fc98.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1109779082" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/reports-that-us-opened-door-for-more-arms-to-kiev-instead-of-peace-troubling---lawmaker-1110473568.html?share-img=1109779082"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / LIBKOS</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Украинские военные с гаубицей M777。 Архивное фото</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Украинские военные с гаубицей M777. Архивное фото - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="Украинские военные с гаубицей M777。 Архивное фото" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3073:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_7dd3b13fccf72222ef1053bec2d7cf6d.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3073:1728_640x0_80_0_0_cbcd9ef950ed12986e002348f069bf24.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3073:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_90faade0c32f646d294dee7be600bfde.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3073:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_7dd3b13fccf72222ef1053bec2d7cf6d.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / LIBKOS </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国众议员保罗·戈萨尔（R-AZ）告诉人造卫星，有关五角大楼使用会计技巧向乌克兰运送更多武器的报道证明国会对安全援助的监督是必要的。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周四，五角大楼发言人萨布丽娜·辛格告诉人造卫星，在审查总统为乌克兰提供的缩编方案时，发现设备估值不一致。媒体报道称，美国可能高估了已向乌克兰提供的安全援助价值 30 亿美元。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “有关五角大楼可能故意高估其发送给乌克兰的军事装备的报道令人深感不安。这种会计噱头只会为向乌克兰提供更多武器打开大门，”戈萨尔说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110473568" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/reports-that-us-opened-door-for-more-arms-to-kiev-instead-of-peace-troubling---lawmaker-1110473568.html?share-block=1110473570" data-title="&quot;Reports that the Pentagon may have purposely overvalued military equipment it sent to Ukraine are deeply troubling. Such accounting gimmicks simply open the door for more weapons being delivered to Ukraine,&quot; Gosar said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位议员表示，美国应该专注于寻找和平解决冲突的办法，而不是向基辅提供更多的军事援助。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我们需要和平，而不是更多致命的武器和更多的杀戮，”戈萨尔说。 “国会监督是有必要的。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110473568" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/reports-that-us-opened-door-for-more-arms-to-kiev-instead-of-peace-troubling---lawmaker-1110473568.html?share-block=1110473572" data-title="&quot;We need peace, not more deadly weapons and more killings,&quot; Gosar said. &quot;Congressional oversight is warranted.&quot; "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">五角大楼表示，在某些情况下，使用重置成本而不是账面净值来评估从美国库存中提取的设备。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">五角大楼网站上的统计数据显示，自乔·拜登总统上任以来，美国已承诺向乌克兰提供超过 300 亿美元的安全援助，该统计数据最后更新于 5 月 3 日。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 00:11:42 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/reports-that-us-opened-door-for-more-arms-to-kiev-instead-of-peace-troubling---lawmaker-1110473568.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/reports-that-us-opened-door-for-more-arms-to-kiev-instead-of-peace-troubling---lawmaker-1110473568.html<category>世界</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>保罗戈萨尔</category><category>五角大楼</category><category>会计错误</category><category>国防部</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Erdogan: Turkiye Does Not Intend to Indulge All Western Demands]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110473444" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0e/1110340165_0:0:2048:3071_1440x900_80_0_1_7a61b954e8b9d93a9c0d2e41af738c43.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1110340147" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/erdogan-turkiye-does-not-intend-to-indulge-all-western-demands-1110473444.html?share-img=1110340147"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Umit Bektas</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安在伊斯坦布尔的一个投票站投票</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan cast his ballot at a polling station in Istanbul - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安在伊斯坦布尔的一个投票站投票" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0e/1110340165_0:0:2048:1153_1920x0_80_0_0_4e31224c10d0b2d71a6356d33582bce2.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0e/1110340165_0:0:2048:1153_640x0_80_0_0_06e92f65a9eaf204267c0819293d0a06.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0e/1110340165_0:0:2048:1153_1280x0_80_0_0_01c66949ffe058ec0cb465e866c08352.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0e/1110340165_0:0:2048:1153_1920x0_80_0_0_4e31224c10d0b2d71a6356d33582bce2.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Umit Bektas </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据伊斯坦布尔（人造卫星）网报道：土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安表示，土耳其不打算满足西方提出的所有要求，特别是在对俄罗斯实施制裁方面。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据最高选举委员会的数据，埃尔多安在本月早些时候举行的第一轮总统选举中获得了 49.24% 的选票，而他的主要竞争对手凯末尔·基利达罗格鲁获得了 45.07% 的选票。 Kilicdaroglu 指责俄罗斯涉嫌干涉土耳其选举。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “反对派表示将重建土耳其与其他国家的关系。一方面，你攻击俄罗斯联邦，另一方面，你说你将重新建立关系，”埃尔多安周五表示。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110473444" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/erdogan-turkiye-does-not-intend-to-indulge-all-western-demands-1110473444.html?share-block=1110473446" data-title="&quot;The opposition says it will rebuild Turkiye's relations with other countries. On the one hand, you attack the Russian Federation, on the other, you say that you will build relations anew,&quot; Erdogan said on Friday. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">土耳其总统指出，安卡拉目前与包括美国在内的所有西方国家以及俄罗斯和中国都保持着关系。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “至于对土耳其最大贸易伙伴俄罗斯的制裁，他们（反对派）说他们会做西方要求的一切。再见凯末尔，土耳其会做我们想做的，而不是西方要求的。这永远不会发生在我们的政治中，”埃尔多安说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110473444" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/erdogan-turkiye-does-not-intend-to-indulge-all-western-demands-1110473444.html?share-block=1110473448" data-title="&quot;As for the sanctions against Turkiye's largest trading partner, Russia, they [the opposition] said that they would do everything demanded by the West. Bye-bye Kemal, Turkiye will do what we want, not what the West demands. This will never happen in our politics,&quot; Erdogan said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">土耳其于5月14日举行议会和总统选举。在清点100%的选票后，土耳其最高选举委员会周一宣布，第二轮总统选举将于5月28日举行，因为没有候选人达到50票％ 临界点。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2020年竞选期间，美国总统拜登承诺如果赢得美国总统大选将支持土耳其反对派，并称埃尔多安是独裁者。对此，土耳其总统发言人易卜拉欣·卡林指责拜登无知、傲慢和虚伪。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 00:02:18 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/erdogan-turkiye-does-not-intend-to-indulge-all-western-demands-1110473444.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/erdogan-turkiye-does-not-intend-to-indulge-all-western-demands-1110473444.html<category>世界</category><category>雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安</category><category>凯末尔·基利达罗格鲁</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>突厥耶</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[British Climber Sets Record 17th Everest Climb by Non-Sherpa Guide]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110472783" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110472881_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_2efbc24c958ed9dfcadd9bf658716124.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110472863" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/british-climber-sets-record-17th-everest-climb-by-non-sherpa-guide-1110472783.html?share-img=1110472863"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Niranjan Shrestha</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">英国登山家 Kenton Cool 于 2023 年 5 月 19 日星期五抵达尼泊尔加德满都机场，他成功完成了他的第 17 次珠穆朗玛峰峰会。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="British mountaineer Kenton Cool who successfully completed his 17th summit of Mount Everest arrives at the airport in Kathmandu, Nepal, Friday, May 19, 2023. - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="2023 年 5 月 19 日星期五，英国登山家 Kenton Cool 成功完成了他第 17 次登顶珠穆朗玛峰，抵达尼泊尔加德满都机场。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110472881_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_499d2de3aa5e3b8c4ee16dd6f32dcaeb.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110472881_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_25e0fb24de312493830006740f441f1e.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110472881_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_0fb5b74c5dd9a7ceb5607c9980c12662.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110472881_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_499d2de3aa5e3b8c4ee16dd6f32dcaeb.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Niranjan Shrestha </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">这位英国登山者于 2004 年首次登上世界最高峰，此后几乎每年都在继续攀登。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">英国登山向导 Kenton Cool 最近第 17 次登上珠穆朗玛峰，打破了他自己的记录，超过了非夏尔巴向导登顶次数最多的山峰。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2004 年首次征服珠穆朗玛峰的库尔在成功完成最近一次攀登后返回尼泊尔首都加德满都。不过，他谦虚地表示，记录不属于高山，强调高山本身更伟大，同时对一次伟大的攀登和安全返回表示满意。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管 Cool 保持着非夏尔巴协作向导的攀登记录，但只有尼泊尔夏尔巴协作超越了他的成就。夏尔巴向导 Kami Rita 最近完成了他的第 27 次攀登，创造了新纪录，而 Pasang Dawa 则 26 次攀登珠穆朗玛峰。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Rita 和 Dawa 仍与他们的登山团队一起在山上，目标可能是在本月晚些时候春季登山季节结束之前再次登顶。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">目前，珠穆朗玛峰上有许多登山者和他们的当地向导，预计未来几周会有大量登山者涌入。尼泊尔当局在本赛季发放了约 470 份登山许可证。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，事实证明，这座山仍然是致命的，因为今年官方记录了数起死亡事件，其中包括四名夏尔巴向导。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>考虑到他的年度攀登数据，Cool 预计将在几年前完成他的第 17 次攀登，但由于过去的赛季被推迟而被推迟。</p><p> 2014 年，由于雪崩夺去了 16 名夏尔巴向导的生命，登山季被取消。第二年，地震引发的雪崩导致 19 人死亡，Cool 无法登顶。此外，由于<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20210423/covid-hits-everest-climber-tests-positive-after-thinking-it-was-altitude-sickness-1082704793.html" target="_blank">COVID-19 大流行，</a> 2020 年登山季<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20200312/china-bans-mount-everest-expeditions-amid-deadly-coronavirus-outbreak-1078552369.html" target="_blank">被取消</a>。</p></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 23:56:33 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/british-climber-sets-record-17th-everest-climb-by-non-sherpa-guide-1110472783.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/british-climber-sets-record-17th-everest-climb-by-non-sherpa-guide-1110472783.html<category>超越政治</category><category>病毒性的</category><category>珠穆朗玛峰</category><category>尼泊尔</category><category>夏尔巴人</category><category>登山</category><category>加德满都</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Astronomers Spot Radiation Belt Outside Solar System for the First Time]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110471308" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110470961_0:0:500:355_1440x900_80_0_1_a55a3d08f1d94b17b5e2dad8065232a1.jpg?source-sid=cc_0" data-photoview-image-id="1110470943" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/astronomers-spot-radiation-belt-outside-solar-system-for-the-first-time-1110471308.html?share-img=1110470943"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> / Chuck Carter, Melodie Kao, Heising-Simons Foundation / <a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-023-06138-w" title="分辨率成像证实了超冷矮星周围的辐射带">解析成像证实了超冷矮星周围的辐射带</a></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">艺术家对极光的印象以及超冷矮星 LSR J1835+3259 周围的辐射带。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_0" alt="Artist’s impression of an aurora and the surrounding radiation belt of the ultracool dwarf LSR J1835+3259. - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="艺术家对超冷矮星 LSR J1835+3259 的极光和周围辐射带的印象。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110470961_0:37:500:318_1920x0_80_0_0_9d021d758b9e30707d9f88564eee0bf8.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110470961_0:37:500:318_640x0_80_0_0_f7e7aeaf99c6848400dc2ead4c4cc06f.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110470961_0:37:500:318_1280x0_80_0_0_1fe2baa7ee768e7014a3d64b42ae32ad.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110470961_0:37:500:318_1920x0_80_0_0_9d021d758b9e30707d9f88564eee0bf8.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> / Chuck Carter, Melodie Kao, Heising-Simons Foundation / <a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-023-06138-w" title="分辨率成像证实了超冷矮星周围的辐射带">解析成像证实超冷矮星周围有一条辐射带</a></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">全球磁场可以捕获宇宙粒子并将它们聚集在行星周围，从而增加行星上出现生命的机会。在一颗遥远的褐矮星上发现了一个这样的场——而且是一个非常强大的场。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">新发现显示，天文学家发现了第一个围绕太阳系外行星观测到的辐射带。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该团队使用了由美国国家射电天文台协调的 39 台射电望远镜阵列和德国马克斯普朗克射电天文学研究所运营的 Effelsberg 射电望远镜。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">距太阳约 18.5 光年的超冷矮星 LSR J1835+3259 的射电图像显示，在天体强大的磁场中被困的高能电子云。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “通过结合来自世界各地的无线电天线，我们可以制作出令人难以置信的高分辨率图像，以看到以前从未见过的东西。我们的图像相当于站在华盛顿特区阅读加利福尼亚州视力表的第一行， “巴克内尔大学的合著者 Jackie Villadsen 说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110471308" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/astronomers-spot-radiation-belt-outside-solar-system-for-the-first-time-1110471308.html?share-block=1110471481" data-title="&amp;quot;By combining radio dishes from across the world, we can make incredibly high-resolution images to see things no one has ever seen before. Our image is comparable to reading the top row of an eye chart in California while standing in Washington, DC,&amp;quot; said coauthor Jackie Villadsen at Bucknell University."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">科学家们在无线电频谱中观察了这颗矮行星，发现一条辐射带的辐射强度比在巨型木星附近发现的辐射带强约 1000 万倍。官方表示从LSR J1835+3259延伸出最多18个半径的距离。<strong>这是落向矮星两极并产生明亮光线的粒子。</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> Melodie 说：“我们实际上是通过观察磁层中的无线电发射等离子体——它的辐射带——对我们目标的磁层成像。对于我们太阳系外的气态巨行星来说，这是以前从未做过的事情。” Kao 是加州大学圣克鲁兹分校的博士后研究员，也是一篇论文的第一作者。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110471308" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/astronomers-spot-radiation-belt-outside-solar-system-for-the-first-time-1110471308.html?share-block=1110471311" data-title="&quot;We are actually imaging the magnetosphere of our target by observing the radio-emitting plasma—its radiation belt—in the magnetosphere. That has never been done before for something the size of a gas giant planet outside of our solar system,&quot; said Melodie Kao, a postdoctoral fellow at UC Santa Cruz and first author of a paper."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为了产生磁场，行星的内部必须足够热以存在导电流体，在地球的情况下，导电流体是其核心中的铁水。在木星上，导电液体是氢，它在如此大的压力下变成了金属。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">高指出，金属氢也可能在褐矮星中产生磁场，而在恒星内部，导电液体是电离氢。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">磁场的强度和形状是决定行星宜居性的重要因素。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “当我们考虑系外行星的宜居性时，除了大​​气和气候等因素外，它们的磁场在维持稳定环境中的作用也是需要考虑的因素，”高说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110471308" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/astronomers-spot-radiation-belt-outside-solar-system-for-the-first-time-1110471308.html?share-block=1110471316" data-title="&amp;quot;When we’re thinking about the habitability of exoplanets, the role of their magnetic fields in maintaining a stable environment is something to consider in addition to things like the atmosphere and climate,&amp;quot; Kao said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">辐射带是行星磁层的一个区域，进入磁层的高能带电粒子聚集并被捕获。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">强磁场在地球周围形成一个“磁泡”——磁层。这会捕获粒子并将其加速到接近光速。太阳系中所有具有磁场的行星，包括地球和木星，都有由这些被行星磁场捕获的高能带电粒子组成的辐射带。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">亚利桑那州立大学的合著者 Evgenya Shkolnik 说：“这是寻找更多此类物体并磨练我们的技能以寻找越来越小的磁层的关键的第一步，最终使我们能够研究那些可能适合居住的地球大小的行星。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110471308" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/astronomers-spot-radiation-belt-outside-solar-system-for-the-first-time-1110471308.html?share-block=1110471319" data-title="&quot;This is a critical first step in finding many more such objects and honing our skills to search for smaller and smaller magnetospheres, eventually enabling us to study those of potentially habitable, Earth-size planets,&quot; said coauthor Evgenya Shkolnik at Arizona State University."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">地球的辐射带被称为范艾伦辐射带。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">观察结果发表在<a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-023-06138-w" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">《自然》</a>杂志上。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 23:22:13 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/astronomers-spot-radiation-belt-outside-solar-system-for-the-first-time-1110471308.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/astronomers-spot-radiation-belt-outside-solar-system-for-the-first-time-1110471308.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>空间</category><category>太空探索</category><category>地球</category><category>国家射电天文台 (NRAO)</category><category>马克斯普朗克研究所</category><category>北极光</category><category>系外行星</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[US Cop Charged for Leaking Police Information to Proud Boys Leader]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110472583" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/04/1110093195_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_a58f045b2a7c6111c1c72ca574cc3035.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110093177" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/us-cop-charged-for-leaking-police-information-to-proud-boys-leader-1110472583.html?share-img=1110093177"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / ALEX EDELMAN</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">美国总统唐纳德特朗普的支持者于 2021 年 1 月 6 日在华盛顿特区的美国国会大厦外抗议。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="Supporters of US President Donald Trump protest outside the US Capitol on January 6, 2021, in Washington, DC.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="美国总统唐纳德特朗普的支持者于 2021 年 1 月 6 日在华盛顿特区的美国国会大厦外抗议。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/04/1110093195_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_3bac04b6ec667cfa8d811605e5098dfc.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/04/1110093195_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_a6d8e39c56651bf91cd41787d2b41ffc.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/04/1110093195_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_3d01c5c62112321e6e51a4acdd3eb5ec.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/04/1110093195_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_3bac04b6ec667cfa8d811605e5098dfc.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / 亚历克斯·埃德尔曼</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国司法部在周五的新闻稿中称，华盛顿大都会警察局（MPD）中尉肖恩·拉蒙德被指控向保守派组织“骄傲男孩”的领导人恩里克·塔里奥泄露信息。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “根据起诉书，拉蒙德担任 MPD 国土安全局情报处的主管。从 2019 年 7 月开始至少持续到 2021 年 1 月，拉蒙德和塔里奥就骄傲男孩计划在哥伦比亚特区开展的活动保持定期联系，”司法部在一份新闻稿中说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">起诉书称，至少早在 2020 年 7 月，拉蒙德就开始使用 Telegram 向塔里奥提供与骄傲男孩在华盛顿的活动有关的执法活动信息。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>新闻稿称，拉蒙德向塔里奥传递了与警方调查 2020 年 12 月 12 日焚烧“黑人的命也是命”横幅事件有关的机密执法信息。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">新闻稿称，当局于 2021 年 1 月对塔里奥发出了逮捕令，当时拉蒙德通过电报通知他逮捕令已经签署。该新闻稿称，两人定期联系，协调骄傲男孩计划在 2019 年 7 月至 2021 年 1 月期间在华盛顿举行的活动。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>司法部还在新闻稿中表示，拉蒙德通过向联邦调查人员作出虚假和误导性陈述来阻挠调查。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">预计拉蒙德将于周五晚些时候在美国哥伦比亚特区地方法院被传讯。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">新闻稿称，妨碍司法罪的法定最高刑期为 30 年，而作出虚假陈述的单一指控可能意味着法定最高刑期为五年。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 22:52:55 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/us-cop-charged-for-leaking-police-information-to-proud-boys-leader-1110472583.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/us-cop-charged-for-leaking-police-information-to-proud-boys-leader-1110472583.html<category>美洲</category><category>司法部</category><category>警视厅</category><category>哥伦比亚特区</category><category>华盛顿</category><category>电报</category><category>骄傲的男孩</category></item></channel></rss>